data.title: NBA Rumors: Deron Williams' Assistant GM Role Will Not Convince Star to Stay
data.meta_description: The  New Jersey Nets  are doing everything in their power to try and persuade  Deron Williams  to re-sign with the franchise. They have even gone as far as to giving him an unofficial title of "assistant general manager...
data.text:
“He’s been involved in the process since December,” GM Billy King said. “We talked about, ‘This is Plan A and this is Plan B and C.’ In training camp he was in my office after practice every day just sitting there. He calls himself, ‘the assistant GM.’ “

“People get traded all the time,” Williams told Yahoo! Sports. “They don’t get backlash as an organization. If [players] leave, we are not loyal, we are ungrateful. People say stuff to me on Twitter. They already think I’m gone. They are out there bashing me, saying to me I’m a traitor. I didn’t ask to be here. I got traded. I didn’t come here being a free agent. This is the first time that I’m a free agent in my career.”
